<title>FRANCE: Paris Metro rides into telecoms.</title>
<headline>Paris Metro rides into telecoms.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Paris metro and bus transport company RATP said on Tuesday it was launching its Telcite telecoms subsidiary with a series of agreements with telecommunications operators.</p>
<p>The Regie Autonome des Transports Parisiens (RATP) owns over 1,000 km of fibre-optic cable in Paris and the central Ile-de-France region which it can rent out as a so-called alternative infrastructure to telecoms operators.</p>
<p>RATP said it had signed deals with Bouygues Telecom, Cegetel as well as MFS/Worldcom. It gave no financial details.</p>
<p>The use of alternative networks, to those of France Telecom, will be possible from January 1, 1998.</p>
